author: RAJ SHEKHAR JHA AND MURARI SHETYE
description: Saurabh and Gaurav Luthra, wanted in connection with a fatal nightclub fire in Goa, are being deported from Thailand to India. The brothers fled the country after the blaze, which claimed 25 lives, and were detained for illegal stay. They are expected to arrive in Delhi and then be taken to Goa for legal proceedings.
title: Goa nightclub fire: Luthra brothers to be deported from Thailand, set to arrive in Delhi today

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: A new IPL rule caps overseas player salaries at INR 18 crore, regardless of auction bids, to enforce financial discipline and prevent inflation.  While franchises pay the full bid amount, the excess goes to the BCCI's player welfare fund, with Indian players remaining unaffected by this cap.
title: IPL Auction: Why Green and other overseas stars can't earn beyond Rs 18 crore - Explained

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Mallika Sagar, a trailblazing auctioneer, will lead the IPL 2026 auction. With a unique career bridging fine art and elite sports, she became Christie's first Indian woman auctioneer in New York. Sagar has since broken barriers in Indian sports, notably as the first female auctioneer for the Pro Kabaddi League and the Women's Premier League.
title: IPL: Who is Mallika Sagar? Meet the woman set to conduct the auction

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Lionel Messi's final India appearance was marked by protests against Delhi's severe air pollution.  Fans chanted about the AQI as Chief Minister Rekha Gupta took the stage.  The hazardous pollution levels were a stark contrast to the celebratory atmosphere for the football icon.  This event highlighted public frustration with the environmental crisis in Delhi-NCR.
title: Messi in Delhi: 'AQI, AQI' chants erupt as crowd targets CM Rekha Gupta - Watch

author: SEHJAL GUPTA
description: Far-right commentator Nick Fuentes reignited his public spat with Candace Owens, making surprising claims about her being in love with him. He also strongly criticized Owens' theories regarding Charlie Kirk's death, dismissing her 'visions' and 'dreams' as evidence. Fuentes expressed sympathy for Charlie Kirk's widow, Erika Kirk, while rejecting Owens' claims about the murder.
title: Nick Fuentes claims ‘chemistry’ with Candace Owens amid Charlie Kirk row

author: BHARTI JAIN
description: The NIA has taken decisive legal action against Lashkar-e-Taiba and The Resistance Front for their involvement in the Pahalgam terror attack. The chargesheet lists seven suspects, featuring the notorious Pakistani handler Sajid Jatt and three deceased militants from Pakistan.
title: Pahalgam attack: Pak handler among 7 named in NIA chargesheet; LeT charged as entity first time

author: DHANANJAY MAHAPATRA
description: The Supreme Court's recent remarks shed light on how the lavish lifestyles of the affluent play a crucial role in the persistent pollution afflicting Delhi-NCR. The court noted a troubling trend: the elite's refusal to reduce their reliance on polluting transportation and gadgets, despite previous rulings designed to address this environmental crisis.
title: Rich’s reluctance to change lifestyle a major reason for pollution, says SC

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: Police have released new details and surveillance footage of a person of interest in the Brown University shooting. The suspect, described as 5'8" with a stocky build, was seen in the area hours before the attack that killed two and injured nine. Authorities confirmed the university was "definitely" targeted, with investigations ongoing into any other potential motives.
title: 'This individual definitely targeted Brown University': Police release new footage, suspect details

author: ANJALI SINGH
description: A speeding biker suffered injuries on NH-8 near Ambience Mall after an alleged unsafe overtaking maneuver. Footage from another rider's helmet camera captured the Suzuki Hayabusa at high velocity before the crash. The rider admitted to overspeeding and wrong-side overtaking, leading to no formal case registration. Traffic police urge adherence to rules on this accident-prone stretch.
title: Gurgaon: Overspeeding bike attempts risky overtake, crashes into cab - video

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Amazon is implementing further job cuts, with a new filing revealing 84 positions are being eliminated in Washington state. These layoffs are separate from the previously announced 14,000 global corporate reductions. The company described the action as a routine organizational review, providing affected employees with 90 days of pay and benefits.
title: Amazon job cuts continue: More roles cut in Washington; engineers, program managers and UX staff affected

author: TNN
title: Joblessness dips to 4.7% in November, lowest since April: Labour data

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: A private jet crashed in San Mateo Atenco, Mexico, during an emergency landing attempt, claiming seven lives. The aircraft, en route from Acapulco to Toluca, struck a business rooftop, igniting a massive fire that necessitated the evacuation of around 130 people. Authorities are still working to recover all bodies from the wreckage.
title: Mexico: 7 killed as private jet hits rooftop during emergency landing

author: MAHIMA ROY
description: Philip Rivers' NFL comeback sparks talk of Tom Brady's potential return.  While Rivers boasts a $100 million net worth from his career and endorsements, Brady's extensive NFL tenure and elite brand deals have reportedly amassed him a staggering $300 million.  Brady appears focused on his broadcasting career, contrasting with Rivers' recent return to the field.
title: Philip Rivers vs Tom Brady net worth: Who earned more in the NFL?

author: TOI NEWS DESK
title: Watch: India rebukes Pakistan at UNSC; says J&K, Ladakh are integral parts of the country
